&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–4 years of Python development with a strong focus on testing, debugging, and code quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience with unit test design: mocking, fixtures, test coverage strategies, edge case handling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with static analysis tools (e.g., pylint, flake8, mypy, SonarQube) and CI/CD pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A clear testing philosophy: ability to articulate trade-offs between test types and coverage strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in a second programming language; JavaScript/Node.js is a strong asset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Systematic debugging approach with the ability to isolate, reproduce, and resolve complex issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s or Master&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nice to have: JavaScript/Node.js experience; familiarity

